This paper discusses the use of clustering heuristics and attribution tags in cryptocurrency analytics, which are commonly used in computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also addresses legal standards and rules for substantiating suspicions and providing evidence in court, which falls under the category of cyber law (cs.CY). The paper also involves data sharing frameworks, which can be related to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
